Classes/AWSKinesisVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).abstract:
An asynchronous API that deletes a stream’s existing edge configuration, as well as the corresponding media from the Edge Agent.

When you invoke this API, the sync status is set to DELETING. A deletion process starts, in which active edge jobs are stopped and all media is deleted from the edge device. The time to delete varies, depending on the total amount of stored media. If the deletion process fails, the sync status changes to DELETE_FAILED. You will need to re-try the deletion.

When the deletion process has completed successfully, the edge configuration is no longer accessible.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).abstract:
Provides an endpoint for the specified signaling channel to send and receive messages. This API uses the SingleMasterChannelEndpointConfiguration input parameter, which consists of the Protocols and Role properties.

Protocols is used to determine the communication mechanism. For example, if you specify WSS as the protocol, this API produces a secure websocket endpoint. If you specify HTTPS as the protocol, this API generates an HTTPS endpoint.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).name: -startEdgeConfigurationUpdate:
Classes/AWSKinesisVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).abstract:
An asynchronous API that updates a stream’s existing edge configuration. The Kinesis Video Stream will sync the stream’s edge configuration with the Edge Agent IoT Greengrass component that runs on an IoT Hub Device, setup at your premise. The time to sync can vary and depends on the connectivity of the Hub Device. The SyncStatus will be updated as the edge configuration is acknowledged, and synced with the Edge Agent.

If this API is invoked for the first time, a new edge configuration will be created for the stream, and the sync status will be set to SYNCING. You will have to wait for the sync status to reach a terminal state such as: IN_SYNC, or SYNC_FAILED, before using this API again. If you invoke this API during the syncing process, a ResourceInUseException will be thrown. The connectivity of the stream’s edge configuration and the Edge Agent will be retried for 15 minutes. After 15 minutes, the status will transition into the SYNC_FAILED state.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).name: -updateDataRetention:
Classes/AWSKinesisVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).abstract:
Increases or decreases the stream’s data retention period by the value that you specify. To indicate whether you want to increase or decrease the data retention period, specify the Operation parameter in the request body. In the request, you must specify either the StreamName or the StreamARN.

The retention period that you specify replaces the current value.

This operation requires permission for the KinesisVideo:UpdateDataRetention action.

Changing the data retention period affects the data in the stream as follows:

  • If the data retention period is increased, existing data is retained for the new retention period. For example, if the data retention period is increased from one hour to seven hours, all existing data is retained for seven hours.

  • If the data retention period is decreased, existing data is retained for the new retention period. For example, if the data retention period is decreased from seven hours to one hour, all existing data is retained for one hour, and any data older than one hour is deleted immediately.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeImageGene.name: imageGenerationConfiguration
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeImageGene.abstract: The structure that contains the information required for the Kinesis video stream (KVS) images delivery. If this structure is null, the configuration will be deleted from the stream.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeImageGene.name: streamARN
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeImageGene.abstract: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Kinesis video stream from which to retrieve the image generation configuration. You must specify either the StreamName or the StreamARN.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeImageGene.name: streamName
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeImageGene.abstract: The name of the stream from which to retrieve the image generation configuration. You must specify either the StreamName or the StreamARN.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.name: creationTime
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.abstract: The timestamp at which a stream’s edge configuration was first created.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.name: edgeAgentStatus
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.abstract: An object that contains the latest status details for an edge agent’s recorder and uploader jobs. Use this information to determine the current health of an edge agent.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.name: edgeConfig
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.abstract: A description of the stream’s edge configuration that will be used to sync with the Edge Agent IoT Greengrass component. The Edge Agent component will run on an IoT Hub Device setup at your premise.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.name: failedStatusDetails
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.abstract: A description of the generated failure status.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.name: lastUpdatedTime
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.abstract: The timestamp at which a stream’s edge configuration was last updated.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.name: streamARN
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.abstract: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the stream.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.name: streamName
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.abstract: The name of the stream from which the edge configuration was updated.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.name: syncStatus
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.abstract: The latest status of the edge configuration update.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.name: streamARN
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.abstract: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the stream. Specify either the StreamNameor the StreamARN.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.name: streamName
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDescribeEdgeConfi.abstract: The name of the stream whose edge configuration you want to update. Specify either the StreamName or the StreamARN.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeletionConfig.ht.name: deleteAfterUpload
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeletionConfig.ht.abstract:
The boolean value used to indicate whether or not you want to mark the media for deletion, once it has been uploaded to the Kinesis Video Stream cloud. The media files can be deleted if any of the deletion configuration values are set to true, such as when the limit for the EdgeRetentionInHours, or the MaxLocalMediaSizeInMB, has been reached.

Since the default value is set to true, configure the uploader schedule such that the media files are not being deleted before they are initially uploaded to the Amazon Web Services cloud.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeletionConfig.ht.name: edgeRetentionInHours
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeletionConfig.ht.abstract: The number of hours that you want to retain the data in the stream on the Edge Agent. The default value of the retention time is 720 hours, which translates to 30 days.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeletionConfig.ht.name: localSizeConfig
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeletionConfig.ht.abstract: The value of the local size required in order to delete the edge configuration.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeleteStreamInput.name: currentVersion
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeleteStreamInput.abstract:
Optional: The version of the stream that you want to delete.

Specify the version as a safeguard to ensure that your are deleting the correct stream. To get the stream version, use the DescribeStream API.

If not specified, only the CreationTime is checked before deleting the stream.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeleteStreamInput.name: streamARN
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeleteStreamInput.abstract: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the stream that you want to delete.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeleteSignalingCh.name: channelARN
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeleteSignalingCh.abstract: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the signaling channel that you want to delete.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeleteSignalingCh.name: currentVersion
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeleteSignalingCh.abstract: The current version of the signaling channel that you want to delete. You can obtain the current version by invoking the DescribeSignalingChannel or ListSignalingChannels API operations.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeleteEdgeConfigu.name: streamARN
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeleteEdgeConfigu.abstract: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the stream. Specify either the StreamName or the StreamARN.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeleteEdgeConfigu.name: streamName
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeleteEdgeConfigu.abstract: The name of the stream from which to delete the edge configuration. Specify either the StreamName or the StreamARN.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateStreamOutpu.name: streamARN
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateStreamOutpu.abstract: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the stream.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateStreamInput.name: dataRetentionInHours
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateStreamInput.abstract:
The number of hours that you want to retain the data in the stream. Kinesis Video Streams retains the data in a data store that is associated with the stream.

The default value is 0, indicating that the stream does not persist data.

When the DataRetentionInHours value is 0, consumers can still consume the fragments that remain in the service host buffer, which has a retention time limit of 5 minutes and a retention memory limit of 200 MB. Fragments are removed from the buffer when either limit is reached.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateStreamInput.name: deviceName
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateStreamInput.abstract:
The name of the device that is writing to the stream.

In the current implementation, Kinesis Video Streams does not use this name.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateStreamInput.name: kmsKeyId
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateStreamInput.abstract:
The ID of the Key Management Service (KMS) key that you want Kinesis Video Streams to use to encrypt stream data.

If no key ID is specified, the default, Kinesis Video-managed key (Amazon Web Services/kinesisvideo) is used.

For more information, see DescribeKey.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateStreamInput.name: mediaType
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateStreamInput.abstract:
The media type of the stream. Consumers of the stream can use this information when processing the stream. For more information about media types, see Media Types. If you choose to specify the MediaType, see Naming Requirements for guidelines.

Example valid values include “video/h264” and “video/h264,audio/aac”.

This parameter is optional; the default value is null (or empty in JSON).

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateStreamInput.name: streamName
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateStreamInput.abstract:
A name for the stream that you are creating.

The stream name is an identifier for the stream, and must be unique for each account and region.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateStreamInput.name: tags
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateStreamInput.abstract: A list of tags to associate with the specified stream. Each tag is a key-value pair (the value is optional).

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateSignalingCh.name: channelARN
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateSignalingCh.abstract: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the created channel.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateSignalingCh.name: channelName
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateSignalingCh.abstract: A name for the signaling channel that you are creating. It must be unique for each Amazon Web Services account and Amazon Web Services Region.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateSignalingCh.name: channelType
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateSignalingCh.abstract: A type of the signaling channel that you are creating. Currently, SINGLE_MASTER is the only supported channel type.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateSignalingCh.name: singleMasterConfiguration
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateSignalingCh.abstract: A structure containing the configuration for the SINGLE_MASTER channel type.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateSignalingCh.name: tags
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoCreateSignalingCh.abstract: A set of tags (key-value pairs) that you want to associate with this channel.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoChannelNameCondit.name: comparisonOperator
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoChannelNameCondit.abstract: A comparison operator. Currently, you can only specify the BEGINS_WITH operator, which finds signaling channels whose names begin with a given prefix.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoChannelInfo.html#.name: channelARN
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoChannelInfo.html#.abstract: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the signaling channel.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoChannelInfo.html#.name: creationTime
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoChannelInfo.html#.abstract: The time at which the signaling channel was created.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoChannelInfo.html#.name: singleMasterConfiguration
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoChannelInfo.html#.abstract: A structure that contains the configuration for the SINGLE_MASTER channel type.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoChannelInfo.html#.name: version
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoChannelInfo.html#.abstract: The current version of the signaling channel.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoChannelInfo.html.name: AWSKinesisVideoChannelInfo
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoChannelInfo.html.abstract: A structure that encapsulates a signaling channel’s metadata and properties.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoChannelNameCondit.name: AWSKinesisVideoChannelNameCondition
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoChannelNameCondit.abstract: An optional input parameter for the ListSignalingChannels API. When this parameter is specified while invoking ListSignalingChannels, the API returns only the channels that satisfy a condition specified in ChannelNameCondition.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeletionConfig.ht.name: AWSKinesisVideoDeletionConfig
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoDeletionConfig.ht.abstract: The configuration details required to delete the connection of the stream from the Edge Agent.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoEdgeAgentStatus.h.name: AWSKinesisVideoEdgeAgentStatus
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoEdgeAgentStatus.h.abstract: An object that contains the latest status details for an edge agent’s recorder and uploader jobs. Use this information to determine the current health of an edge agent.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoEdgeConfig.html.name: AWSKinesisVideoEdgeConfig
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoEdgeConfig.html.abstract: A description of the stream’s edge configuration that will be used to sync with the Edge Agent IoT Greengrass component. The Edge Agent component will run on an IoT Hub Device setup at your premise.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoImageGenerationCo.name: AWSKinesisVideoImageGenerationConfiguration
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoImageGenerationCo.abstract: The structure that contains the information required for the KVS images delivery. If null, the configuration will be deleted from the stream.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoImageGenerationDe.name: AWSKinesisVideoImageGenerationDestinationConfig
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoImageGenerationDe.abstract: The structure that contains the information required to deliver images to a customer.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoLastRecorderStatu.name: AWSKinesisVideoLastRecorderStatus
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoLastRecorderStatu.abstract: The latest status of a stream’s edge recording job.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoLastUploaderStatu.name: AWSKinesisVideoLastUploaderStatus
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoLastUploaderStatu.abstract: The latest status of a stream’s edge to cloud uploader job.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoListEdgeAgentConf.name: AWSKinesisVideoListEdgeAgentConfigurationsEdgeConfig
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoListEdgeAgentConf.abstract: A description of a single stream’s edge configuration.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoLocalSizeConfig.h.name: AWSKinesisVideoLocalSizeConfig
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoLocalSizeConfig.h.abstract: The configuration details that include the maximum size of the media (MaxLocalMediaSizeInMB) that you want to store for a stream on the Edge Agent, as well as the strategy that should be used (StrategyOnFullSize) when a stream’s maximum size has been reached.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoMappedResourceCon.name: AWSKinesisVideoMappedResourceConfigurationListItem
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoMappedResourceCon.abstract: A structure that encapsulates, or contains, the media storage configuration properties.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoMediaSourceConfig.name: AWSKinesisVideoMediaSourceConfig
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoMediaSourceConfig.abstract: The configuration details that consist of the credentials required (MediaUriSecretArn and MediaUriType) to access the media files that are streamed to the camera.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoMediaStorageConfi.name: AWSKinesisVideoMediaStorageConfiguration
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoMediaStorageConfi.abstract: A structure that encapsulates, or contains, the media storage configuration properties.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoNotificationConfi.name: AWSKinesisVideoNotificationConfiguration
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoNotificationConfi.abstract: The structure that contains the notification information for the KVS images delivery. If this parameter is null, the configuration will be deleted from the stream.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoNotificationDesti.name: AWSKinesisVideoNotificationDestinationConfig
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoNotificationDesti.abstract: The structure that contains the information required to deliver a notification to a customer.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoRecorderConfig.ht.name: AWSKinesisVideoRecorderConfig
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoRecorderConfig.ht.abstract: The recorder configuration consists of the local MediaSourceConfig details that are used as credentials to accesss the local media files streamed on the camera.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoResourceEndpointL.name: AWSKinesisVideoResourceEndpointListItem
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoResourceEndpointL.abstract:
An object that describes the endpoint of the signaling channel returned by the GetSignalingChannelEndpoint API.

The media server endpoint will correspond to the WEBRTC Protocol.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoScheduleConfig.ht.name: AWSKinesisVideoScheduleConfig
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoScheduleConfig.ht.abstract:
This API enables you to specify the duration that the camera, or local media file, should record onto the Edge Agent. The ScheduleConfig consists of the ScheduleExpression and the DurationInMinutes attributes.

If the ScheduleConfig is not provided in the RecorderConfig, then the Edge Agent will always be set to recording mode.

If the ScheduleConfig is not provided in the UploaderConfig, then the Edge Agent will upload at regular intervals (every 1 hour).

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoSingleMasterChann.name: AWSKinesisVideoSingleMasterChannelEndpointConfiguration
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoSingleMasterChann.abstract: An object that contains the endpoint configuration for the SINGLE_MASTER channel type.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoSingleMasterConfi.name: AWSKinesisVideoSingleMasterConfiguration
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoSingleMasterConfi.abstract: A structure that contains the configuration for the SINGLE_MASTER channel type.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoStreamInfo.html.name: AWSKinesisVideoStreamInfo
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoStreamInfo.html.abstract: An object describing a Kinesis video stream.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoStreamNameConditi.name: AWSKinesisVideoStreamNameCondition
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoStreamNameConditi.abstract: Specifies the condition that streams must satisfy to be returned when you list streams (see the ListStreams API). A condition has a comparison operation and a value. Currently, you can specify only the BEGINS_WITH operator, which finds streams whose names start with a given prefix.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoTag.html.name: AWSKinesisVideoTag
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoTag.html.abstract: A key and value pair that is associated with the specified signaling channel.

Classes/AWSKinesisVideoUploaderConfig.ht.name: AWSKinesisVideoUploaderConfig
Classes/AWSKinesisVideoUploaderConfig.ht.abstract: The configuration that consists of the ScheduleExpression and the DurationInMinutes details that specify the scheduling to record from a camera, or local media file, onto the Edge Agent. If the ScheduleConfig is not provided in the UploaderConfig, then the Edge Agent will upload at regular intervals (every 1 hour).
